-- Spurs Defeat Grizzlies 104-93 in OT for 3-0 NBA Playoffs Lead
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-05-26T05:01:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-26/spurs-defeat-grizzlies-104-93-in-ot-for-3-0-nba-playoffs-lead.html
Tim Duncan scored 24 points,
including seven of the team’s 18 in overtime, as the San Antonio
Spurs defeated the Memphis Grizzlies 104-93 in the National
Basketball Association playoffs.  The Spurs won the first three games in the best-of-seven
Western Conference series and can advance with a victory
tomorrow to the championship game against the Miami Heat or
Indiana Pacers.  In today’s game, the Heat visit the Pacers to try to break
the 1-1 tie in their Eastern Conference series.  The Grizzlies jumped out to a 16-point first-quarter lead
as they held the Spurs to 13 points. Memphis ended the first
half with a 44-40 advantage even though they were outscored
27-15 in the second quarter.  Memphis guard Tony Allen hit a free throw with 33 seconds
left to tie the score at 86-86 and force the game into overtime
when his teammate Mike Conley missed a basket at the buzzer on
their home court at FedExForum.  Tony Parker scored 26 points for the Spurs and Manu Ginobili came off the bench to add 19 points.  Conley scored 20 points and Marc Gasol had 16 points and 14
rebounds for the Grizzlies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
